					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
	
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>

		
			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=1118">Kaladim</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Bloodforge Hammer</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Bloodforge Hammer</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=3421"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:">Adory</a> | 
		                        1/7/2000 4:49:28 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Bloodforge Hammer is very slow, but has excellent stats - and is rather valuable to sell as well. It also glows like a greater lightstone - making it a nice weapon for barbarian types.<BR>
<BR>
Anyway - once your faction with the warriors guild in Kaladim is up to amiable - you can do this quest. See Byzel Bloodforge - he tells you a tale of woo about Trumpy Irontoe - and how he ran off on his sister - anyway, he wants his head, badly.<BR>
<BR>
Several other quests require this head as well - Trumpy isn't difficult, his protectors are.<BR>
<BR>
Find Trumpy in Qeynos - in a tavern. Get him drunk, he will wander out onto the docks - kick something in the water, then kill him. Note: This will likely make you KOS in that bar - and his protectors are VERY mean.<BR>
<BR>
My husband did this quest, was KOS in the bar after 3 attempts. My best suggestion is to find someone that can root - or bring enough people to just blast him - if you give him a chance to run back to the bar, you've got a problem.<BR>
<BR>
This is the first quest I've seen that really has something decent as a reward - but /con Byzal first, I don't think it works if your not at least amiable to him.<BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
