			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				As of 3-27-2000, This quest is still working /grin<BR>
A couple of notes:<BR>
First, as a level 14, most of the Corrupt Guards con blue or green, so they are not really too much trouble. I follow Trumpy (after asking who is sragg), to what seemed like a pretty remote spot, then rooted him w/grasping roots and started wailing on him. Unbeknowst to me, a corrupt guard had been behind me, and started wailing on ME. I concentrated on killing Trumpy. (This was my 3rd try. Rooting is REQUIRED. The little bugger runs pretty fast when he's scared :)). When he died, I quick-looted his head, didn't bother with the other stuff, and conned the guard -blue. I made a quick decision no to fight him (I'm sure I could've taken him, but didn't want the extra faction hit, and didn't want to take the chance of another guard walking by), so I just ran for zone. I had SoW up, so no problem getting away. The corrupt guards were dubious to me both before and after I killed Trumpy.<BR>
Second, I had trouble finding what to say to Bloodforge to make him give the quest, (I'm still not sure if that is actually required, but after such a LONG trip, I wasn't taking any chances),  it is on one of these posts, but I had trouble finding it, so I will re-post it. &quot;I am willing to take a little trip.&quot; There you go.<BR>
Last, I had warmly faction with Bloodforge (must've been all those CB belts I went from 7 to 10 with :)). That is my recomendation for faction with stormguard -CB belts and lego pads. Crushbone is crowded, yes, but still pretty fun. (Unless you are insanely high level, then why would you want this weapon, anyway?)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
